	<article class="post-86432 post type-post status-publish hentry category-dashboard tag-entrepreneurship tag-small-business tag-united-states-economy des-entrepreneurship des-small-business des-united-states-economy" id="post-86432">
	<header class="postHeader">
				<div class="postKicker">
					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Why Innovation Is Overrated</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-06-17T16:18:39+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">June 17, 2014 12:18 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">June 17, 2014 12:18 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/06/17/today-in-small-business-why-innovation-is-overrated/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Why Innovation Is Overrated" data-description="When brick-and-mortar businesses act like start-ups. When middle schoolers act like Avon ladies. And why deregulation doesn&#039;t help entrepreneurs. ">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Office construction in New York reached its <a href="//www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20140616/REAL_ESTATE/140619895/office-construction-hits-fastest-pace-since-1990">fastest pace since</a> 1990, and the <a href="//econintersect.com/a/blogs/blog1.php/june-2014-empire-state-survey">latest survey</a> on the state&#8217;s manufacturing activity improved marginally.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ <a href="//seekingalpha.com/article/2270873-nahb-homebuilder-sentiment-better-than-expected">Homebuilder sentiment</a> is better than expected.</p>
